@diafygi: I don't think it will work since you only check for `valid` after you waited that `pending` goes away. The problem here is that the `http-01` challenge will be `pending` forever since another challenge is already `valid`. I think you can simply fix this by testing the value of `authorization['status']`  against `"valid"` right after you obtain `authorization` the first time (https://github.com/diafygi/acme-tiny/blob/master/acme_tiny.py#L125). If it is already valid, there's no need to execute the rest of the loop body.

I guess this can be done with +1 line by executing https://github.com/diafygi/acme-tiny/blob/master/acme_tiny.py#L129-L147 only if `authorization['status'] != "valid"`.

(Also, this can speed up getting a new certificate because it can happen quite often that verifications for at least some of the domains are still valid; then there's no need to re-validate them.)

