@stephenrauch Even if we implement `query_env` as an attribute correctly now, there's still the danger that somebody will forget about the invariants and use it as a persistent attribute later. Passing function arguments through a transient object attribute that gets assigned behind the scenes is quite counter-intuitive.

Tree is a graph where there is exactly one (unoriented) path between any pair of vertices. Directed acyclic graph is an oriented graph that contains no oriented cycles but there may exist multiple distinct oriented paths between a pair of vertices (all paths going in the same direction). See [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Directed_acyclic_graph) for details and examples.

In other words, a structure of `Expression` objects may not be a tree because two distinct paths from the root can converge at the same subexpression.

For questions, please submit on MXNet discussion forum (https://discuss.mxnet.io), where it will get a wider audience and allow other to learn as well.
