I would put:

#include <cassert>
#include <limits>
#include <type_traits>

template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_integral<T>::value>>
inline T Cast(size_t value)
{
	assert(value <= static_cast<size_t>(std::numeric_limits<T>::max()));
	return static_cast<T>(value);
}

in types.h to the global namespace in the first #ifdef __cplusplus block. Now you can call this cast function, so you get rid of the warnings and even get notified at runtime when the cast goes wrong. Whenever you have time for actually revisiting all these decisions, you can simply search for "Cast<" and you will find all places that you have to revisit.

